@DATABASE "Motos"
@NODE "MAIN" "SPECCY POKES - M - Motos"
@TOC "MAIN"

                   ZX SPECTRUM (SPECCY heheh) POKES - M
                   ====================================

                                   Motos
                                   =====



DESCRIPTION              POKE
===========              ====

@{"Infinite Lives  " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(42241,0)"}        42241,0
@{"Infinite Energy " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(42462,0)"}        42462,0
@{"Infinite Jumps  " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(42473,0)"}        42473,0
@{"Lives = x       " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(33300,255)"}        33300,x (x= 1-255)
@{"Start Same Level" RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(33288,0)"}        33288,0

                         The "Star Same Level" POKE is only really
                         useful if you aren't using Infinite Lives
                         as it restarts you on the level you died
                         on, instead of back to level 1.

                         However, because of the way the POKE works,
                         you have to have a normal game BEFORE using
                         the POKE, as the variables aren't set up
                         at first, and it tries to start the game
                         on level 0, and crashes.

                         Rastan.
@endnode
